EXTENDED OUTLOOK
TUESDAY TO FRIDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND
COASTGUARD AGENCY AT 232300 UTC
THROUGH TUESDAY EVENING AND WEDNESDAY A RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE WILL EXTEND
FM SIBERIA ACROSS SCANDINAVIA THE N SEA AND UK AND TOWARDS MID ATLANTIC
ALTHOUGH MIGRATING SWARDS ACROSS THE UK ON WEDNESDAY. LOW PRESSURE WILL LIE
ACROSS EERN EUROPE AS WELL AS TO THE W OF
IBERIA AND A DEEP AREA 972 NEAR ICELAND. A SIMILAR PRESSURE PATTERN WILL
PERSIST THROUGH THURSDAY AND FRIDAY ALTHOUGH WITH A TRANSITORY TROUGH OF
LOW PRESSURE RUNNING ACROSS THE UK THURSDAY. AN AREA OF HIGH PRESSURE WILL
THEN BUILD ONCE MORE ACROSS THE S OF THE UK ON
FRIDAY. ON TUESDAY EVENING STRG WINDS WILL DEVELOP IN NERN SEA AREAS WITH
GALES POSS IN VIKING AND FAIR ISLE. STRG WINDS ARE THEN EXP TO EXTEND SWARDS
ACROSS ALL AREAS DURING WEDNESDAY AND THURSDAY. OCCASIONAL GALES WILL CONTINUE
IN VIKING N UTSIRE AND FAIR ISLE POSSIBLY SEV GALES ON THURSDAY. ON FRIDAY
GALES ARE POSS N OF 55N
